This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it presents a new approach to ensemble learning that involves constructing and applying different predictive models to different subsets of the feature space. It also reports the results of experiments on a variety of datasets, which is a common practice in machine learning research. 

The paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as ensemble learning is a popular technique in AI and the paper proposes a new approach to improve its performance. 

The sub-category of data mining (cs.DM) is also a possibility as ensemble learning is often used in data mining applications. 

The sub-category of statistics (cs.ST) may be relevant as the paper establishes loss bounds for the final predictor in terms of the Rademacher complexity of the base learners, which is a statistical measure. 

Finally, the sub-category of computational engineering (cs.CE) may be relevant as the paper proposes a new approach to improve the performance of machine learning algorithms, which can have practical applications in various engineering fields.
